Second Department,

October, 1959

(October 5, 1959) The People of the State of New York, Respondent, v. Herbert Borum, Appellant.

Motion to dismiss appeal from an order denying a motion in the nature of a writ of coram nobis. Motion to dismiss appeal granted by default and appeal dismissed. Present — Nolan, P. J., Wenzel, Beldock, Ughetta and Hallinan, JJ.
